
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconColor Blue

class Patient {
  - patientID: String
  - name: String
  - consentGiven: Boolean
}

class Doctor {
  - doctorID: String
  - name: String
  - specialty: String
}

class HeadDoctor {
  - headDoctorID: String
  - name: String
}

class Illness {
  - illnessID: String
  - name: String
  - priorityScore: Priority (High | Low)
}

class Diagnosis {
  - diagnosisID: String
  - illnessID: String
  - doctorID: String
  - approvedByHeadDoctor: Boolean
}

class Treatment {
  - treatmentID: String
  - illnessID: String
  - stage: Stage (Stage1 | Stage2 | Stage3)
  - patientID: String
}

class ConsentForm {
  - consentID: String
  - patientID: String
  - signedDate: Date
}

enum Stage {
  Stage1
  Stage2
  Stage3
}

enum Priority {
  High
  Low
}

Patient "1" -- "0..*" Diagnosis : has
Doctor "1" -- "0..*" Diagnosis : makes
HeadDoctor "1" -- "0..*" Diagnosis : approves

Illness "1" -- "0..*" Diagnosis : related to
Illness "1" -- "0..*" Treatment : related to

Diagnosis "1" -- "0..*" Treatment : applies to

Treatment "1" -- "0..1" ConsentForm : requires consent

Patient "1" -- "0..*" ConsentForm : signs
@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Relationships:

- A `Patient` can have multiple `Diagnoses`, each made by a `Doctor`.
- Each `Diagnosis` must be approved by a `HeadDoctor` before any `Treatment` can be applied.
- An `Illness` is associated with one or more `Diagnoses` and `Treatments`.
- A `Treatment` has a `Stage` (Stage1, Stage2, Stage3), and can be upgraded based on:
  - Patient consent (once given, all treatments for that patient can be upgraded freely).
  - Illness `PriorityScore` (if set to **High**, all treatments for that illness are automatically moved to Stage3).
- A `ConsentForm` is used to allow a `Patient` to upgrade treatments from Stage1 to higher stages.

